ls.py`\n25:    - 14 дЄ™еПѓйАЙе≠ЧжЃµпЉМжО•жФґ CLI еСљдї§и°МйАЙй°є\n26:    - `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any])` з±їжЦєж≥ХдїОе≠ЧеЕЄжЮДйА†\n27: \n28: 3. **`MetadataService` з±їеЃЮзО∞**\n29:    - `load_metadata(workspace_path)` вАФ жМЙ `agent_metadata.yaml` вЖТ `agent.yaml` вЖТ `metadata.yaml` дЉШеЕИзЇІеЫЮйААеК†иљљ\n30:    - `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` вАФ еЖЩеЕ• `agent_metadata.yaml`пЉМдљњзФ® `yaml.dump(default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)`\n31:    - `update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` вАФ еК†иљљ вЖТ еРИеєґ вЖТ й™МиѓБ вЖТ дњЭе≠Ш вЖТ ињФеЫЮ\n32:    - `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` вАФ иЈѓеЊДе≠ШеЬ®жАІ + иѓ≠и®АзЙєеЃЪж†°й™М\n33:    - `_validate_python_workspace()` вАФ и¶Бж±ВиЗ≥е∞СдЄАдЄ™ `*.py` жЦЗдїґ\n34:    - `_validate_java_workspace()` вАФ и¶Бж±В `pom.xml` е≠ШеЬ®\n35: \n36: 4. **жЬНеК°йЫЖжИР**\n37:    - жЫіжЦ∞ `agentcube/services/__init__.py` еѓЉеЗЇ `MetadataService` еТМ `AgentMetadata`\n38:    - `PackRuntime` йАЪињЗ `MetadataService` еК†иљљ/еИЫеїЇ/дњЭе≠ШеЕГжХ∞жНЃ\n39:    - `BuildRuntime` / `PublishRuntime` / `InvokeRuntime` / `StatusRuntime` ж≠£з°Ѓи∞ГзФ® `MetadataService`\n40: \n41: 5. **йФЩиѓѓе§ДзРЖ**\n42:    - еЈ•дљЬз©ЇйЧідЄНе≠ШеЬ® вЖТ `ValueError`\n43:    - Python еЈ•дљЬз©ЇйЧіжЧ† `.py` жЦЗдїґ вЖТ `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n44:    - Java еЈ•дљЬз©ЇйЧіжЧ† `pom.xml` вЖТ `ValueError`\n45:    - YAML иІ£жЮРе§±иі• вЖТ еМЕи£ЕдЄЇжЬЙжДПдєЙзЪДйФЩиѓѓ\n46:    - Pydantic й™МиѓБе§±иі• вЖТ дЉ†жТ≠ ValidationError\n47: \n48: ### дЄНеМЕеРЂ\n49: \n50: - еЕГжХ∞жНЃзЙИжЬђињБзІїеЈ•еЕЈпЉИеРОзї≠ ARпЉЙ\n51: - е§ЪеЈ•дљЬз©ЇйЧіеЕГжХ∞жНЃиБЪеРИ\n52: - ињЬз®ЛеЕГжХ∞жНЃеРМж≠•\n53: - еЕГжХ∞жНЃеК†еѓЖе≠ШеВ®\n54: - Go CLI жИЦеЕґдїЦиѓ≠и®А SDK зЪДеЕГжХ∞жНЃжЬНеК°\n55: \n56: ## жЮґжЮДж¶Ви¶Б\n57: \n58: ### жХ∞жНЃжµБ\n59: \n60: ```\n61: CLI Command (pack/build/publish/invoke/status)\n62:     вФВ\n63:     вЦЉ\n64: Runtime Class (PackRuntime/BuildRuntime/...)\n65:     вФВ\n66:     вФЬвФАвФА MetadataService.load_metadata() вФАвФАвЖТ agent_metadata.yaml (YAML)\n67:     вФВ         вФВ                                    вФВ\n68:     вФВ         вЦЉ                                    вФВ\n69:     вФВ    AgentMetadata (Pydantic) вЧДвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФШ\n70:     вФВ         вФВ\n71:     вФВ         вФЬвФАвФА CLI options merge (MetadataOptions)\n72:     вФВ         вФВ\n73:     вФВ         вФЬвФАвФА validate_workspace()\n74:     вФВ         вФВ\n75:     вФВ         вФФвФАвФА MetadataService.save_metadata() вФАвФАвЖТ agent_metadata.yaml\n76:     вФВ\n77:     вФФвФАвФА дЄЪеК°йАїиЊСпЉИзФЯжИР DockerfileгАБжЮДеїЇйХЬеГПгАБйГ®зљ≤з≠ЙпЉЙ\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### ж†ЄењГз±їеЕ≥з≥ї\n81: \n82: | з±ї | иБМиі£ | дЊЭиµЦ |\n83: |----|------|------|\n84: | `AgentMetadata` | еЕГжХ∞жНЃеЉЇз±їеЮЛж®°еЮЛпЉМPydantic й™МиѓБ | Pydantic |\n85: | `MetadataOptions` | CLI йАЙй°єеИ∞еЕГжХ∞жНЃзЪДиљђжНҐдЄ≠йЧіе±В | dataclasses |\n86: | `MetadataService` | еЕГжХ∞жНЃ CRUD + workspace й™МиѓБ | AgentMetadata, yaml, pathlib |\n87: | `PackRuntime` | жЙУеМЕжµБз®ЛзЉЦжОТ | MetadataService, DockerService |\n88: | `BuildRuntime` | жЮДеїЇжµБз®ЛзЉЦжОТ | MetadataService, DockerService |\n89: | `PublishRuntime` | еПСеЄГжµБз®ЛзЉЦжОТ | MetadataService, KubernetesProvider, AgentCubeProvider |\n90: | `InvokeRuntime` | и∞ГзФ®жµБз®ЛзЉЦжОТ | MetadataService |\n91: | `StatusRuntime` | зКґжАБжЯ•иѓҐзЉЦжОТ | MetadataService |\n92: \n93: ### AgentMetadata е≠ЧжЃµеЃЪдєЙ\n94: \n95: | е≠ЧжЃµ | з±їеЮЛ | йїШиЃ§еАЉ | иѓіжШО |\n96: |------|------|--------|------|\n97: | `agent_name` | `str` | ењЕе°Ђ | Agent еФѓдЄАж†ЗиѓЖ |\n98: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | дЇЇз±їеПѓиѓїжППињ∞ |\n99: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | зЉЦз®Лиѓ≠и®АпЉИpython/javaпЉЙ |\n100: | `entrypoint` | `str` | ењЕе°Ђ | еРѓеК®еСљдї§ |\n101: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | жЪійЬ≤зЂѓеП£пЉИ1-65535пЉЙ |\n102: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | жЮДеїЇз≠ЦзХ•пЉИlocal/cloudпЉЙ |\n103: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | йГ®зљ≤еМЇеЯЯ |\n104: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | иѓ≠дєЙеМЦзЙИжЬђ |\n105: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | еЃєеЩ®йХЬеГПдњ°жБѓ |\n106: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | иЃ§иѓБйЕНзљЃ |\n107: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python дЊЭиµЦжЦЗдїґ |\n108: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | йХЬеГПдїУеЇУ URL |\n109: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | дїУеЇУзФ®жИЈеРН |\n110: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | дїУеЇУеѓЖз†Б |\n111: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent зЂѓзВє URL |\n112: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL |\n113: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL |\n114: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | е∞±зї™жОҐйТИиЈѓеЊД |\n115: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | е∞±зї™жОҐйТИзЂѓеП£ |\n116: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | AgentCube еИЖйЕНзЪД ID |\n117: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | дЉЪиѓЭ ID |\n118: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | K8s йГ®зљ≤дњ°жБѓ |\n119: \n120: ### MetadataOptions е≠ЧжЃµеЃЪдєЙ\n121: \n122: | е≠ЧжЃµ | з±їеЮЛ | йїШиЃ§еАЉ |\n123: |------|------|--------|\n124: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n125: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n126: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n127: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n128: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n129: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n130: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n131: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n132: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n133: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n134: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n135: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n136: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n137: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n138: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n139: \n140: ### YAML жМБдєЕеМЦж†ЉеЉПз§ЇдЊЛ\n141: \n142: ```yaml\n143: agent_name: hello-agent\n144: description: A simple hello world agent\n145: language: python\n146: entrypoint: python main.py\n147: port: 8080\n148: build_mode: local\n149: version: \"0.1.0\"\n150: image:\n151:   name: hello-agent\n152:   tag: \"0.1.0\"\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ## дЄКжЄЄдЊЭиµЦ\n156: \n157: | дЊЭиµЦ | зФ®йАФ | ељ±еУН |\n158: |------|------|------|\n159: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata ж®°еЮЛеЃЪдєЙдЄОй™МиѓБ | еЈ≤жЬЙдЊЭиµЦпЉМжЧ†жЦ∞еҐЮ |\n160: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML еЇПеИЧеМЦ/еПНеЇПеИЧеМЦ | еЈ≤жЬЙдЊЭиµЦпЉМжЧ†жЦ∞еҐЮ |\n161: | `packaging>=23.0` | зЙИжЬђеПЈйАТеҐЮпЉИbuild еСљдї§дљњзФ®пЉЙ | еЈ≤жЬЙдЊЭиµЦпЉМжЧ†жЦ∞еҐЮ |\n162: \n163: ### еПЧељ±еУНзЪДзїДдїґ\n164: \n165: - **`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`**пЉИдњЃжФє/жЦ∞еҐЮпЉЙпЉЪ`MetadataService` з±ї + `AgentMetadata` ж®°еЮЛ\n166: - **`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`**пЉИжЦ∞еҐЮпЉЙпЉЪ`MetadataOptions` dataclass\n167: - **`agentcube/services/__init__.py`**пЉИдњЃжФєпЉЙпЉЪеѓЉеЗЇ `MetadataService`гАБ`AgentMetadata`\n168: - **`agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`**пЉИдњЃжФєпЉЙпЉЪеѓЉеЗЇ `MetadataOptions`\n169: - **`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`**пЉИдњЃжФєпЉЙпЉЪйАЪињЗ `MetadataService` жУНдљЬеЕГжХ∞жНЃ\n170: - **`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`**пЉИдњЃжФєпЉЙпЉЪйАЪињЗ `MetadataService` еК†иљљ/жЫіжЦ∞еЕГжХ∞жНЃ\n171: - **`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`**пЉИдњЃжФєпЉЙпЉЪйАЪињЗ `MetadataService` еК†иљљ/жЫіжЦ∞еЕГжХ∞жНЃ\n172: - **`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`**пЉИдњЃжФєпЉЙпЉЪйАЪињЗ `MetadataService` еК†иљљеЕГжХ∞жНЃ\n173: - **`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`**пЉИдњЃжФєпЉЙпЉЪйАЪињЗ `MetadataService` еК†иљљеЕГжХ∞жНЃ\n174: \n175: ### й£ОйЩ©иѓДдЉ∞\n176: \n177: | й£ОйЩ© | з≠ЙзЇІ | зЉУиІ£жО™жЦљ |\n178: |------|------|----------|\n179: | жЧІзЙИ `agentcube.yaml` жЦЗдїґдЄНеЕЉеЃє | дЄ≠ | е§ЪжЦЗдїґеРНеЫЮйААеК†иљљ + ињБзІїжПРз§Ї |\n180: | Pydantic v2 API еПШжЫі | дљО | йФБеЃЪ `pydantic>=2.0.0`пЉМдљњзФ®з®≥еЃЪ API |\n181: | еєґеПСеЖЩеЕ•еЖ≤з™Б | дљО | еНХзФ®жИЈ CLI еЈ•еЕЈпЉМй£ОйЩ©дљОпЉЫеПѓеК†жЦЗдїґйФБ |\n182: | еЕГжХ∞жНЃе≠ЧжЃµзЉЇе§±еѓЉиЗідЄЛжЄЄйФЩиѓѓ | дЄ≠ | Pydantic й™МиѓБ + еРИзРЖйїШиЃ§еАЉ |\n183: \n184: ## зКґжАБ\n185: \n186: - [ ] жПРж°ИеЃ°жЯ•\n187: - [ ] еЃЮзО∞\n188: - [ ] й™МиѓБ\n\n(End of file - total 188 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 вАФ MetadataService дЄОжХ∞жНЃж®°еЮЛ\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli\n**Language:** Python\n**Size:** M\n\n## зЫЃзЪД\n\nдЄЇ AgentCube CLI еЃЮзО∞еЕГжХ∞жНЃжЬНеК°е±ВдЄОж†ЄењГжХ∞жНЃж®°еЮЛпЉМжПРдЊЫ workspace еЕГжХ∞жНЃзЪДеК†иљљгАБдњЭе≠ШгАБй™МиѓБеТМжЫіжЦ∞иГљеКЫпЉМжФѓжТС `pack`гАБ`build`гАБ`publish`гАБ`invoke`гАБ`status` еЕ®зФЯеСљеС®жЬЯзЪДеЕГжХ∞жНЃзЃ°зРЖгАВ\n\nељУеЙН CLI еРД Runtime з±їйЬАи¶БиѓїеЖЩ workspace дЄ≠зЪД agent йЕНзљЃдњ°жБѓпЉМдљЖзЉЇдєПзїЯдЄАзЪДжЬНеК°жКљи±°еТМеЉЇз±їеЮЛжХ∞жНЃж®°еЮЛгАВжЬђ AR еЬ® `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` дЄ≠еЃЮзО∞ `MetadataService` з±їпЉМеЬ® `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` дЄ≠еЃЪдєЙ `MetadataOptions` dataclassпЉМеєґдљњзФ® Pydantic `BaseModel` еЃЪдєЙ `AgentMetadata` ж®°еЮЛгАВ\n\n## иМГеЫі\n\n### еМЕеРЂ\n\n1. **`AgentMetadata` Pydantic ж®°еЮЛ**\n   - еЃЪдєЙеЬ® `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`пЉИжИЦзЛђзЂЛж®°еЭЧпЉЙ\n   - 22 дЄ™е≠ЧжЃµи¶ЖзЫЦ agent еРНзІ∞гАБиѓ≠и®АгАБеЕ•еП£гАБзЂѓеП£гАБжЮДеїЇж®°еЉПгАБйХЬеГПгАБиЃ§иѓБгАБзЂѓзВєгАБжОҐйТИгАБK8s йГ®зљ≤з≠Й\n   - 3 дЄ™ validatorsпЉЪ`validate_language`пЉИpython/javaпЉЙгАБ`validate_build_mode`пЉИlocal/cloudпЉЙгАБ`validate_port`пЉИ1-65535пЉЙ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775861190188,"end":1775861190201}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861191540,"sessionID":"ses_2866cdffeffebbLEVIAe132gIZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79934e9d001iFmKyu1TX2suaV","messageID":"msg_d79933edf001RiI5w9NR1fY3Jv","sessionID":"ses_2866cdffeffebbLEVIAe132gIZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_614b33aaa30d4aa280fce6e3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 вАФ MetadataService дЄОжХ∞жНЃж®°еЮЛ вАФ Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This design specifies the full technical implementation of the metadata service layer and core data models for the AgentCube CLI. It covers three components:\n6: \n7: 1. **`AgentMetadata`** вАФ Pydantic `BaseModel` with 22 fields, 3 validators (`language`, `build_mode`, `port`), and `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` for YAML serialization.\n8: 2. **`MetadataOptions`** вАФ dataclass with 14 optional fields and a `from_options()` classmethod for CLI-to-model conversion.\n9: 3. **`MetadataService`** вАФ service class providing `load_metadata()`, `save_metadata()`, `update_metadata()`, `validate_workspace()`, and language-specific workspace validation.\n10: \n11: These components form the foundation for all CLI lifecycle commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`) вАФ each Runtime class reads/writes workspace metadata through `MetadataService` rather than direct file I/O.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ### 2.1 Data Flow\n18: \n19: ```\n20: вФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР\n21: вФВ                        CLI Commands (Typer)                           вФВ\n22: вФВ   pack / build / publish / invoke / status                            вФВ\n23: вФФвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФђвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФШ\n24:                              вФВ\n25:           вФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФівФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР\n26:           вЦЉ                                     вЦЉ\n27: вФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР             вФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР\n28: вФВ    Runtime Class    вФВ             вФВ   MetadataOptions   вФВ\n29: вФВ  (PackRuntime etc)  вФВ             вФВ   (CLI вЖТ dataclass) вФВ\n30: вФВ                     вФВ             вФФвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФђвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФШ\n31: вФВ .pack() / .build()  вФВ                        вФВ\n32: вФВ .publish() / etc    вФВ                        вЦЉ\n33: вФВ                     вФВ             вФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР\n34: вФВ  вФЬвФА MetadataService вФВвЧДвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФВ  asdict(opts)       вФВ\n35: вФВ  вФВ   .load_metadata()             вФВ  merge into updates  вФВ\n36: вФВ  вФВ   .save_metadata()             вФФвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФШ\n37: вФВ  вФВ   .update_metadata()\n38: вФВ  вФВ   .validate_workspace()        вФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР\n39: вФВ  вФФвФА Business logic                вФВ   AgentMetadata     вФВ\n40: вФВ     (Dockerfile, build, etc)      вФВ   (Pydantic model)  вФВ\n41: вФФвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФШ             вФФвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФђвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФШ\n42:                                                вФВ\n43:                               вФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФівФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР\n44:                               вЦЉ                                 вЦЉ\n45:                     вФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР            вФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР\n46:                     вФВ  YAML file I/O   вФВ            вФВ  Validation      вФВ\n47:                     вФВ  agent_metadata. вФВ            вФВ  language:       вФВ\n48:                     вФВ    yaml вЖРвЖТ       вФВ            вФВ  build_mode:     вФВ\n49:                     вФВ  AgentMetadata   вФВ            вФВ  port: 1-65535   вФВ\n50:                     вФФвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФШ            вФФвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФШ\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ### 2.2 Package Layout\n54: \n55: ```\n56: cmd/cli/\n57: вФЬвФАвФА pyproject.toml                         вАФ Dependencies (pydantic, pyyaml already declared)\n58: вФЬвФАвФА agentcube/\n59: вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА __init__.py                        вАФ __version__, exports (no MetadataService/AgentMetadata)\n60: вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА cli/\n61: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА __init__.py                    вАФ Subpackage marker\n62: вФВ   вФВ   вФФвФАвФА main.py                        вАФ Typer app, commands, _handle_error\n63: вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА models/\n64: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА __init__.py                    вАФ Subpackage marker\n65: вФВ   вФВ   вФФвФАвФА pack_models.py                 вАФ MetadataOptions dataclass (EXISTING)\n66: вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА runtime/\n67: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА __init__.py                    вАФ Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\n68: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА pack_runtime.py                вАФ PackRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n69: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА build_runtime.py               вАФ BuildRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n70: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА publish_runtime.py             вАФ PublishRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n71: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА invoke_runtime.py              вАФ InvokeRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n72: вФВ   вФВ   вФФвФАвФА status_runtime.py              вАФ StatusRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n73: вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА services/\n74: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА __init__.py                    вАФ Services package docstring\n75: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА metadata_service.py            вАФ AgentMetadata + MetadataService (EXISTING)\n76: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА docker_service.py              вАФ DockerService\n77: вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА k8s_provider.py                вАФ KubernetesProvider\n78: вФВ   вФВ   вФФвФАвФА agentcube_provider.py          вАФ AgentCubeProvider\n79: вФВ   вФФвФАвФА operations/\n80: вФВ       вФФвФАвФА __init__.py                    вАФ Placeholder module docstring\n81: вФФвФАвФА tests/\n82:     вФЬвФАвФА services/\n83:     вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА test_metadata_service.py       вАФ MetadataService unit tests (EXISTING)\n84:     вФВ   вФФвФАвФА test_metadata_model.py         вАФ AgentMetadata Pydantic tests (EXISTING)\n85:     вФФвФАвФА models/\n86:         вФФвФАвФА test_pack_models.py            вАФ MetadataOptions tests (EXISTING)\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ### 2.3 Dependencies\n90: \n91: | Dependency | Version | Purpose | Status |\n92: |------------|---------|---------|--------|\n93: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | `AgentMetadata` model definition, `field_validator`, `model_dump`, `model_copy` | Already declared |\n94: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | `yaml.safe_load()`, `yaml.dump()` for metadata file I/O | Already declared |\n95: | `dataclasses` | stdlib | `MetadataOptions` dataclass, `asdict()` | stdlib, no install needed |\n96: | `pathlib` | stdlib | `Path` for workspace path handling | stdlib, no install needed |\n97: \n98: No new dependencies are introduced.\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Component Design\n103: \n104: ### 3.1 AgentMetadata (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n105: \n106: ```python\n107: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n108:     \"\"\"Pydantic model representing agent metadata.\"\"\"\n109: \n110:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n111:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n112:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n113:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n114:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n115:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n116:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n117:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n118:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n119:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n120:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n121:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n122:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n123:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n124:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n125:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n126:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n127:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n128:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n129:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n130:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n131:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n132: ```\n133: \n134: #### 3.1.1 Field Categories\n135: \n136: | Category | Fields | Notes |\n137: |----------|--------|-------|\n138: | **Required** | `agent_name`, `entrypoint` | Must be provided at construction; no defaults |\n139: | **Validated enums** | `language`, `build_mode` | Normalized to lowercase; restricted to allowed values |\n140: | **Validated range** | `port` | Must be in `1..65535` |\n141: | **String defaults** | `requirements_file`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password` | Non-empty string defaults for operational fields |\n142: | **Optional (None)** | `description`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment` | Excluded from YAML output when `None` |\n143: \n144: #### 3.1.2 Validators\n145: \n146: ```python\n147: @field_validator(\"language\", mode=\"before\")\n148: @classmethod\n149: def validate_language(cls, v: Optional[str]) -> str:\n150:     \"\"\"Normalize to lowercase; accept only 'python' or 'java'.\"\"\"\n151:     if v is None:\n152:         return \"python\"\n153:     lowered = v.lower()\n154:     if lowered not in (\"python\", \"java\"):\n155:         raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'.\")\n156:     return lowered\n157: \n158: @field_validator(\"build_mode\", mode=\"before\")\n159: @classmethod\n160: def validate_build_mode(cls, v: Optional[str]) -> str:\n161:     \"\"\"Normalize to lowercase; accept only 'local' or 'cloud'.\"\"\"\n162:     if v is None:\n163:         return \"local\"\n164:     lowered = v.lower()\n165:     if lowered not in (\"local\", \"cloud\"):\n166:         raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'.\")\n167:     return lowered\n168: \n169: @field_validator(\"port\")\n170: @classmethod\n171: def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n172:     \"\"\"Validate port is within valid TCP range.\"\"\"\n173:     if v < 1 or v > 65535:\n174:         raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n175:     return v\n176: ```\n177: \n178: **Design decisions:**\n179: - `mode=\"before\"` on `language` and `build_mode` validators ensures normalization happens before Pydantic's type coercion, allowing `None` вЖТ default mapping.\n180: - `port` validator uses default mode (after type coercion) since the field is already `int`.\n181: \n182: #### 3.1.3 Serialization\n183: \n184: ```python\n185: # To dict for YAML вАФ excludes None fields to keep output clean\n186: data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n187: \n188: # To create a modified copy (used by update_metadata and callers)\n189: updated = metadata.model_copy(update={\"port\": 9090, \"description\": \"new\"})\n190: ```\n191: \n192: ### 3.2 MetadataOptions (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n193: \n194: ```python\n195: @dataclass\n196: class MetadataOptions:\n197:     \"\"\"CLI options that map to AgentMetadata fields.\"\"\"\n198: \n199:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n200:     language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n201:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n202:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n203:     build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n204:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n205:     description: Optional[str] = None\n206:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n207:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n208:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n209:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n210:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n211:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n212:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n213:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n214: ```\n215: \n216: #### 3.2.1 `from_options()` classmethod\n217: \n218: ```python\n219: @classmethod\n220: def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n221:     \"\"\"Create a MetadataOptions instance from a dict of CLI options.\n222: \n223:     Unknown fields are silently ignored. This allows callers to pass\n224:     the full **options dict from Typer commands without filtering.\n225:     \"\"\"\n226:     known_fields = {\n227:         \"agent_name\", \"language\", \"entrypoint\", \"port\", \"build_mode\",\n228:         \"requirements_file\", \"description\", \"workload_manager_url\",\n229:         \"router_url\", \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\",\n230:         \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\",\n231:     }\n232:     filtered = {k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in known_fields}\n233:     return cls(**filtered)\n234: ```\n235: \n236: **Design decisions:**\n237: - All fields are `Optional` so that `None` values can be distinguished from explicit defaults during merge logic.\n238: - String fields use `\"\"` as default (not `None`) for URL/path-type fields that should never be `None` in operational contexts.\n239: - `from_options()` silently ignores unknown keys вАФ this is intentional to allow `**options` passthrough from Typer commands which may include `verbose`, `output`, etc.\n240: \n241: #### 3.2.2 Usage in PackRuntime\n242: \n243: ```python\n244: # In PackRuntime.pack():\n245: opts = MetadataOptions.from_options(options)\n246: options_dict = asdict(opts)\n247: \n248: metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options_dict)\n249: metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options_dict)\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### 3.3 MetadataService (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n253: \n254: ```python\n255: class MetadataService:\n256:     \"\"\"Service for loading, saving, and updating agent metadata files.\"\"\"\n257: \n258:     METADATA_FILES: List[str] = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n259: \n260:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n261:         self.verbose = verbose\n262: ```\n263: \n264: #### 3.3.1 `load_metadata(workspace_path: Path) -> Optional[AgentMetadata]`\n265: \n266: ```python\n267: def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Optional[AgentMetadata]:\n268:     \"\"\"Load agent metadata from the workspace directory.\n269: \n270:     Tries files in order: agent_metadata.yaml вЖТ agent.yaml вЖТ metadata.yaml.\n271:     Returns None if no metadata file exists.\n272: \n273:     Raises:\n274:         yaml.YAMLError: If the found file contains malformed YAML.\n275:         ValidationError: If the YAML content fails Pydantic validation.\n276:     \"\"\"\n277:     for filename in self.METADATA_FILES:\n278:         filepath = workspace_path / filename\n279:         if filepath.exists():\n280:             with open(filepath, \"r\") as f:\n281:                 data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n282:             if data is None:\n283:                 data = {}\n284:             return AgentMetadata(**data)\n285:     return None\n286: ```\n287: \n288: **Key behaviors:**\n289: - Returns `None` (not a default `AgentMetadata`) when no file exists вАФ callers must decide whether to create defaults.\n290: - Handles empty YAML files (`yaml.safe_load` returns `None`) by treating as empty dict.\n291: - Does **not** catch `yaml.YAMLError` or `ValidationError` вАФ these propagate to callers for appropriate error handling.\n292: \n293: #### 3.3.2 `save_metadata(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n294: \n295: ```python\n296: def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n297:     \"\"\"Save agent metadata to agent_metadata.yaml in the workspace directory.\n298: \n299:     Uses yaml.dump with:\n300:     - default_flow_style=False (block style, human-readable)\n301:     - indent=2 (2-space indentation)\n302:     - sort_keys=False (preserves model field definition order)\n303:     - model_dump(exclude_none=True) (omits None fields from output)\n304:     \"\"\"\n305:     filepath = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n306:     data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n307:     with open(filepath, \"w\") as f:\n308:         yaml.dump(data, f, default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)\n309: ```\n310: \n311: **Key behaviors:**\n312: - Always writes to `agent_metadata.yaml` (the canonical filename), regardless of which file was loaded.\n313: - Overwrites existing file without backup.\n314: - `exclude_none=True` ensures clean YAML output without `field: null` entries.\n315: \n316: #### 3.3.3 `update_metadata(workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata`\n317: \n318: ```python\n319: def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n320:     \"\"\"Load existing metadata (or create default), apply updates, save, and return.\n321: \n322:     If no metadata file exists, creates a new AgentMetadata using the provided\n323:     updates for required fields (agent_name, entrypoint) and defaults for the rest.\n324: \n325:     Raises:\n326:         ValidationError: If the merged data fails Pydantic validation.\n327:     \"\"\"\n328:     existing = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n329:     if existing is None:\n330:         existing = AgentMetadata(\n331:             agent_name=updates.get(\"agent_name\", workspace_path.name),\n332:             entrypoint=updates.get(\"entrypoint\", \"\"),\n333:             language=updates.get(\"language\", \"python\"),\n334:             port=updates.get(\"port\", 8080),\n335:             build_mode=updates.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n336:         )\n337:     merged = existing.model_copy(update=updates)\n338:     self.save_metadata(workspace_path, merged)\n339:     return merged\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **Key behaviors:**\n343: - Uses `model_copy(update=...)` for immutable merge вАФ Pydantic validates the result.\n344: - When creating defaults, uses `workspace_path.name` as fallback for `agent_name`.\n345: - Validation errors from `model_copy()` propagate to callers.\n346: \n347: #### 3.3.4 `validate_workspace(workspace_path: Path) -> bool`\n348: \n349: ```python\n350: def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n351:     \"\"\"Check if the workspace has valid metadata.\n352: \n353:     Returns True if any metadata file exists and can be loaded, False otherwise.\n354:     Note: This does NOT validate filesystem structure вАФ only metadata file presence.\n355:     \"\"\"\n356:     return self.load_metadata(workspace_path) is not None\n357: ```\n358: \n359: **Design note:** This method checks metadata file existence, not filesystem validity. Language-specific workspace validation (`.py` files, `pom.xml`) is handled by `_validate_python_workspace` and `_validate_java_workspace`.\n360: \n361: #### 3.3.5 `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n362: \n363: ```python\n364: def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n365:     \"\"\"Validate a Python workspace has required files.\n366: \n367:     Requires:\n368:     - At least one *.py file in the workspace root\n369:     - The requirements file (from metadata.requirements_file or default \"requirements.txt\")\n370:     \"\"\"\n371:     py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n372:     if not py_files:\n373:         raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n374:     req_file = metadata.requirements_file or \"requirements.txt\"\n375:     req_path = workspace_path / req_file\n376:     if not req_path.exists():\n377:         raise ValueError(f\"Dependency file not found: {req_file}\")\n378: ```\n379: \n380: #### 3.3.6 `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n381: \n382: ```python\n383: def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n384:     \"\"\"Validate a Java workspace has required files.\n385: \n386:     Requires:\n387:     - pom.xml in the workspace root\n388:     \"\"\"\n389:     pom = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n390:     if not pom.exists():\n391:         raise ValueError(\"pom.xml is required for Java projects\")\n392: ```\n393: \n394: **Note:** `MetadataService` validates presence of `pom.xml` but does not parse XML. `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility()` additionally parses `pom.xml` with `xml.etree.ElementTree` to verify well-formedness.\n395: \n396: ---\n397: \n398: ## Data Flow Details\n399: \n400: ### 4.1 Pack Command Metadata Flow\n401: \n402: ```\n403: CLI pack(workspace, agent_name, language, entrypoint, port, ...)\n404:   вФВ\n405:   вФЬвФАвФА PackRuntime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n406:   вФВ     вФВ\n407:   вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА _validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n408:   вФВ     вФВ     вФФвФАвФА check path exists and is directory\n409:   вФВ     вФВ\n410:   вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА MetadataOptions.from_options(options) вЖТ opts\n411:   вФВ     вФВ     вФФвФАвФА asdict(opts) вЖТ options_dict\n412:   вФВ     вФВ\n413:   вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА _load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options_dict)\n414:   вФВ     вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА MetadataService.load_metadata() вЖТ existing or None\n415:   вФВ     вФВ     вФФвФАвФА if None: create AgentMetadata from options_dict\n416:   вФВ     вФВ\n417:   вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА _apply_option_overrides(metadata, options_dict)\n418:   вФВ     вФВ     вФФвФАвФА metadata.model_copy(update={non-None, non-empty values})\n419:   вФВ     вФВ\n420:   вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА infer entrypoint if missing\n421:   вФВ     вФВ\n422:   вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА _validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n423:   вФВ     вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА python вЖТ _validate_python_compatibility()\n424:   вФВ     вФВ     вФВ     вФФвФАвФА check *.py files exist\n425:   вФВ     вФВ     вФФвФАвФА java вЖТ _validate_java_compatibility()\n426:   вФВ     вФВ           вФФвФАвФА check pom.xml exists and is valid XML\n427:   вФВ     вФВ\n428:   вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА _process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n429:   вФВ     вФВ\n430:   вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА _generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n431:   вФВ     вФВ     вФФвФАвФА generate Python or Java Dockerfile if none exists\n432:   вФВ     вФВ\n433:   вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА _update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n434:   вФВ     вФВ     вФФвФАвФА MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n435:   вФВ     вФВ\n436:   вФВ     вФФвФАвФА _prepare_output_path(workspace_path, output)\n437:   вФВ\n438:   вФФвФАвФА Return: {agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path, dockerfile_path, output_path}\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### 4.2 Build/Publish/Invoke/Status Metadata Flow\n442: \n443: ```\n444: CLI build/publish/invoke/status(workspace, ...)\n445:   вФВ\n446:   вФФвФАвФА Runtime.build/publish/invoke/get_status(workspace_path, ...)\n447:         вФВ\n448:         вФЬвФАвФА MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n449:         вФВ     вФФвФАвФА AgentMetadata or None\n450:         вФВ\n451:         вФЬвФАвФА Business logic uses metadata fields:\n452:         вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА build:    metadata.version, metadata.build_mode, metadata.image\n453:         вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА publish:  metadata.agent_name, metadata.version, metadata.k8s_deployment\n454:         вФВ     вФЬвФАвФА invoke:   metadata.agent_id, metadata.agent_endpoint, metadata.session_id\n455:         вФВ     вФФвФАвФА status:   metadata.agent_id, metadata.k8s_deployment\n456:         вФВ\n457:         вФФвФАвФА MetadataService.save_metadata() or update_metadata() (if state changes)\n458: ```\n459: \n460: ### 4.3 YAML Serialization Format\n461: \n462: **Input (AgentMetadata instance):**\n463: ```python\n464: AgentMetadata(\n465:     agent_name=\"hello-agent\",\n466:     description=\"A simple hello world agent\",\n467:     language=\"python\",\n468:     entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n469:     port=8080,\n470:     build_mode=\"local\",\n471:     version=\"0.1.0\",\n472:     image={\"name\": \"hello-agent\", \"tag\": \"0.1.0\"},\n473: )\n474: ```\n475: \n476: **Output (agent_metadata.yaml):**\n477: ```yaml\n478: agent_name: hello-agent\n479: description: A simple hello world agent\n480: language: python\n481: entrypoint: python main.py\n482: port: 8080\n483: build_mode: local\n484: version: 0.1.0\n485: image:\n486:   name: hello-agent\n487:   tag: 0.1.0\n488: ```\n489: \n490: Note: `version` is serialized as `0.1.0` (float-like) by PyYAML. This is a known behavior; the value round-trips correctly as a string when loaded back because Pydantic coerces it.\n491: \n492: ---\n493: \n494: ## Error Handling\n495: \n496: ### 5.1 Error Matrix\n497: \n498: | Scenario | Error Type | Message | Raised By |\n499: |----------|-----------|---------|-----------|\n500: | No metadata file found | Returns `None` | вАФ | `load_metadata()` |\n501: | Malformed YAML | `yaml.YAMLError` | PyYAML's native error | `load_metadata()` |\n502: | Unsupported language | `ValidationError` | `\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'.\"` | `AgentMetadata.validate_language` |\n503: | Unsupported build mode | `ValidationError` | `\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'.\"` | `AgentMetadata.validate_build_mode` |\n504: | Port out of range | `ValidationError` | `\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\"` | `AgentMetadata.validate_port` |\n505: | Missing required field | `ValidationError` | Pydantic's native `\"Field required\"` | `AgentMetadata` construction |\n506: | No Python files | `ValueError` | `\"No Python files found in workspace\"` | `_validate_python_workspace()` |\n507: | Missing requirements file | `ValueError` | `\"Dependency file not found: {req_file}\"` | `_validate_python_workspace()` |\n508: | Missing pom.xml | `ValueError` | `\"pom.xml is required for Java projects\"` | `_validate_java_workspace()` |\n509: \n510: ### 5.2 Error Propagation Strategy\n511: \n512: - **`MetadataService`** does not wrap errors вАФ it lets `yaml.YAMLError`, `ValidationError`, and `ValueError` propagate to callers.\n513: - **Runtime classes** catch errors at their boundary and re-raise as `RuntimeError` or let them bubble to the CLI layer.\n514: - **CLI layer** uses `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` to format errors with Rich markup and exit code 1.\n515: \n516: ### 5.3 Verbose Logging\n517: \n518: The `verbose` flag on `MetadataService` is stored but not actively used for logging in the current implementation. Future enhancement: add `logging.debug()` calls in `load_metadata`, `save_metadata`, and `update_metadata` when `self.verbose` is `True`.\n519: \n520: ---\n521: \n522: ## Testing Strategy\n523: \n524: ### 6.1 Test Coverage Matrix\n525: \n526: #### AgentMetadata Tests (`tests/services/test_metadata_model.py`)\n527: \n528: | Test Class | Scenarios |\n529: |------------|-----------|\n530: | `TestAgentMetadataValidCreation` | Minimal required fields only; all fields provided |\n531: | `TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage` | `python`/`java` accepted; `Python`/`Java` normalized; `nodejs`/`ruby` rejected |\n532: | `TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode` | `local`/`cloud` accepted; `LOCAL` normalized; `hybrid` rejected |\n533: | `TestAgentMetadataValidatePort` | `1`, `8080`, `65535` accepted; `0`, `70000` rejected |\n534: | `TestAgentMetadataModelDump` | `exclude_none=True` omits None fields; required/defaults present |\n535: \n536: #### MetadataOptions Tests (`tests/models/test_pack_models.py`)\n537: \n538: | Test Class | Scenarios |\n539: |------------|-----------|\n540: | `TestMetadataOptionsDefaults` | All 14 fields have expected defaults |\n541: | `TestMetadataOptionsFromOptions` | Full dict; partial dict; unknown fields ignored; empty dict |\n542: \n543: #### MetadataService Tests (`tests/services/test_metadata_service.py`)\n544: \n545: | Test Class | Scenarios |\n546: |------------|-----------|\n547: | `TestLoadMetadataPrimaryExists` | Loads from `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n548: | `TestLoadMetadataFirstFallback` | Falls back to `agent.yaml` |\n549: | `TestLoadMetadataSecondFallback` | Falls back to `metadata.yaml` |\n550: | `TestLoadMetadataNoneExist` | Returns `None` when no file exists |\n551: | `TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip` | Save then load produces same values |\n552: | `TestSaveMetadataExcludeNone` | No `null` values in YAML output |\n553: | `TestSaveMetadataFormat` | 2-space indent, no trailing whitespace |\n554: | `TestUpdateMetadataMerge` | Partial update preserves existing fields |\n555: | `TestUpdateMetadataCreateNew` | Creates new metadata when no file exists |\n556: \n557: ### 6.2 Test Fixtures\n558: \n559: ```python\n560: @pytest.fixture\n561: def service() -> MetadataService:\n562:     return MetadataService()\n563: \n564: @pytest.fixture\n565: def workspace_with_primary(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n566:     ws = tmp_path / \"ws-primary\"\n567:     ws.mkdir()\n568:     (ws / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n569:         \"agent_name: primary-agent\\nlanguage: python\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nport: 8080\\nbuild_mode: local\\n\"\n570:     )\n571:     (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n572:     return ws\n573: \n574: @pytest.fixture\n575: def workspace_with_fallback1(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n576:     ws = tmp_path / \"ws-fb1\"\n577:     ws.mkdir()\n578:     (ws / \"agent.yaml\").write_text(\n579:         \"agent_name: fallback1-agent\\nlanguage: java\\nentrypoint: java -jar app.jar\\nport: 9090\\nbuild_mode: cloud\\n\"\n580:     )\n581:     (ws / \"pom.xml\").write_text(\"<project></project>\\n\")\n582:     return ws\n583: \n584: @pytest.fixture\n585: def workspace_with_fallback2(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n586:     ws = tmp_path / \"ws-fb2\"\n587:     ws.mkdir()\n588:     (ws / \"metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n589:         \"agent_name: fallback2-agent\\nlanguage: python\\nentrypoint: python app.py\\nport: 3000\\nbuild_mode: local\\n\"\n590:     )\n591:     (ws / \"app.py\").write_text(\"print('hi')\\n\")\n592:     return ws\n593: \n594: @pytest.fixture\n595: def empty_workspace(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n596:     ws = tmp_path / \"ws-empty\"\n597:     ws.mkdir()\n598:     return ws\n599: ```\n600: \n601: ### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n602: \n603: - **Filesystem:** Use `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated, auto-cleaned temporary directories.\n604: - **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external dependencies вАФ only `yaml` and `pathlib`).\n605: - **AgentMetadata:** Real Pydantic model (validators are pure functions, no side effects).\n606: - **MetadataOptions:** Real dataclass (pure data transformation).\n607: \n608: No mocking is needed for the core metadata layer вАФ all components are pure functions or simple file I/O.\n609: \n610: ### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n611: \n612: 1. `pytest tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -v` вАФ all pass\n613: 2. `pytest tests/services/test_metadata_model.py -v` вАФ all pass\n614: 3. `pytest tests/models/test_pack_models.py -v` вАФ all pass\n615: 4. `ruff check agentcube/services/metadata_service.py agentcube/models/pack_models.py` вАФ no violations\n616: 5. `mypy agentcube/services/metadata_service.py agentcube/models/pack_models.py` вАФ no type errors\n617: 6. Round-trip test: save вЖТ load produces equivalent field values\n618: 7. All three validators tested for both acceptance and rejection cases\n619: \n620: ---\n621: \n622: ## Implementation Notes\n623: \n624: 1. **`AgentMetadata` location**: Defined in `metadata_service.py` (not a separate `metadata_models.py`) because the model is tightly coupled to the service вАФ it is the service's primary input/output type. This matches the existing codebase pattern.\n625: \n626: 2. **`model_copy(update=...)` vs manual merge**: Pydantic v2's `model_copy(update=...)` is preferred over manual dict merging because it preserves type safety and re-runs validators on updated fields.\n627: \n628: 3. **`None` vs `\"\"` defaults in MetadataOptions**: URL-type fields (`workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, etc.) default to `\"\"` rather than `None` because downstream code (e.g., `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides`) checks `value is not None and value != \"\"` to determine whether to apply an override. This allows CLI defaults to be distinguished from \"not provided.\"\n629: \n630: 4. **YAML version serialization**: PyYAML serializes `\"0.1.0\"` as `0.1.0` (unquoted, parsed as float on load). Pydantic's `str` type coercion handles this on reload. If strict string preservation is needed in the future, a custom YAML representer could be added.\n631: \n632: 5. **File fallback priority**: `agent_metadata.yaml` вЖТ `agent.yaml` вЖТ `metadata.yaml`. The primary file (`agent_metadata.yaml`) is always the write target, regardless of which file was loaded. This ensures gradual migration from legacy filenames.\n633: \n634: 6. **`validate_workspace` naming**: Despite the name, `MetadataService.validate_workspace()` only checks for metadata file presence. Actual filesystem validation (`.py` files, `pom.xml`) is done by `_validate_python_workspace` and `_validate_java_workspace`, called from `PackRuntime._validate_language_compatibility()`.\n635: \n636: 7. **No concurrent write protection**: As a single-user CLI tool, file locking is not implemented. If concurrent access becomes a concern, `fcntl.flock()` could be added to `save_metadata`.\n637: \n638: 8. **`services/__init__.py` exports**: Currently the file contains only a docstring. `MetadataService` and `AgentMetadata` are imported directly from `agentcube.services.metadata_service` by consumers (e.g., `PackRuntime`). No re-exports are added in this AR.\n639: \n640: 9. **`runtime/__init__.py` exports**: Re-exports `MetadataOptions` from `agentcube.models.pack_models` for convenience:\n641:    ```python\n642:    from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\n643:    __all__ = [\"PackRuntime\", \"BuildRuntime\", \"PublishRuntime\", \"InvokeRuntime\", \"StatusRuntime\", \"MetadataOptions\"]\n644:    ```\n645: \n646: 10. **Integration with existing Runtime classes**: All Runtime classes already import and use `MetadataService` and `AgentMetadata` from their canonical locations. No import path changes are needed вАФ this AR documents and solidifies the existing implementation.\n\n(End of file - total 646 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 вАФ MetadataService дЄОжХ∞жНЃж®°еЮЛ вАФ Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design specifies the full technical implementation of the metadata service layer and core data models for the AgentCube CLI. It covers three components:\n\n1. **`AgentMetadata`** вАФ Pydantic `BaseModel` with 22 fields, 3 validators (`language`, `build_mode`, `port`), and `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` for YAML serialization.\n2. **`MetadataOptions`** вАФ dataclass with 14 optional fields and a `from_options()` classmethod for CLI-to-model conversion.\n3. **`MetadataService`** вАФ service class providing `load_metadata()`, `save_metadata()`, `update_metadata()`, `validate_workspace()`, and language-specific workspace validation.\n\nThese components form the foundation for all CLI lifecycle commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`) вАФ each Runtime class reads/writes workspace metadata through `MetadataService` rather than direct file I/O.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Data Flow\n\n```\nвФМвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/design.md","time":{"start":1775861191528,"end":1775861191536}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861192915,"sessionID":"ses_2866cdffeffebbLEVIAe132gIZ","part":{"id":"prt_d799353f4001hnViE4vdXOcd0K","messageID":"msg_d79933edf001RiI5w9NR1fY3Jv","sessionID":"ses_2866cdffeffebbLEVIAe132gIZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01815a79df634df7bb3606a8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025: MetadataService дЄОжХ∞жНЃж®°еЮЛ вАФ Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: AgentMetadata Pydantic model\n13: \n14: The system SHALL define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` with typed fields, defaults, descriptions, and validators for language, build_mode, and port.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Construct with required fields only\n17: - **GIVEN** input `agent_name=\"test-agent\"` and `entrypoint=\"main.py\"`\n18: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(agent_name=\"test-agent\", entrypoint=\"main.py\")` is constructed\n19: - **THEN** the instance SHALL have defaults `language=\"python\"`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=\"local\"`, `requirements_file=\"requirements.txt\"`, `registry_url=\"\"`, `registry_username=\"\"`, `registry_password=\"\"`, and all `Optional` fields as `None`\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Construct with all fields\n22: - **GIVEN** a complete dict of all `AgentMetadata` fields\n23: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(**fields)` is constructed\n24: - **THEN** the instance SHALL have all fields set to the provided values\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Required field agent_name missing\n27: - **GIVEN** no `agent_name` is provided\n28: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(entrypoint=\"main.py\")` is constructed\n29: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` for missing required field `agent_name`\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Required field entrypoint missing\n32: - **GIVEN** no `entrypoint` is provided\n33: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(agent_name=\"test\")` is constructed\n34: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` for missing required field `entrypoint`\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: validate_language normalizes case\n37: - **GIVEN** input `language=\"Python\"`\n38: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n39: - **THEN** the `validate_language` validator SHALL normalize to `\"python\"`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: validate_language accepts java\n42: - **GIVEN** input `language=\"JAVA\"`\n43: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n44: - **THEN** the validator SHALL normalize to `\"java\"` and accept it\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: validate_language rejects unsupported language\n47: - **GIVEN** input `language=\"go\"`\n48: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n49: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating only `['python', 'java']` are allowed\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: validate_build_mode normalizes case\n52: - **GIVEN** input `build_mode=\"Cloud\"`\n53: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n54: - **THEN** the `validate_build_mode` validator SHALL normalize to `\"cloud\"`\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: validate_build_mode rejects unsupported mode\n57: - **GIVEN** input `build_mode=\"hybrid\"`\n58: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n59: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating only `['local', 'cloud']` are allowed\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: validate_port accepts valid range\n62: - **GIVEN** input `port=8080`\n63: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n64: - **THEN** the `validate_port` validator SHALL accept it (within `1..65535`)\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: validate_port accepts boundary minimum\n67: - **GIVEN** input `port=1`\n68: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n69: - **THEN** the validator SHALL accept it\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: validate_port accepts boundary maximum\n72: - **GIVEN** input `port=65535`\n73: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n74: - **THEN** the validator SHALL accept it\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: validate_port rejects zero\n77: - **GIVEN** input `port=0`\n78: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n79: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` for port below minimum `1`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: validate_port rejects above maximum\n82: - **GIVEN** input `port=70000`\n83: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n84: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` for port above maximum `65535`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Optional fields default to None\n87: - **GIVEN** only required fields are provided\n88: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n89: - **THEN** fields `description`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment` SHALL all be `None`\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: MetadataOptions dataclass\n94: \n95: The system SHALL define `MetadataOptions` as a dataclass with a `from_options` classmethod for dict-to-dataclass conversion, used to capture CLI override options.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: from_options with full dict\n98: - **GIVEN** a dict `{\"agent_name\": \"my-agent\", \"language\": \"java\", \"port\": 9090, \"entrypoint\": \"mvn run\"}`\n99: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options_dict)` is called\n100: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a `MetadataOptions` instance with those fields set and remaining fields at their defaults (`language='python'`, `port=8080`, `build_mode='local'`)\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: from_options with empty dict\n103: - **GIVEN** an empty dict `{}`\n104: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options_dict)` is called\n105: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a `MetadataOptions` instance with all fields at defaults\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: from_options with unknown keys ignored\n108: - **GIVEN** a dict containing keys not in `MetadataOptions` fields (e.g., `{\"verbose\": True}`)\n109: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options_dict)` is called\n110: - **THEN** the system SHALL ignore unknown keys and construct the instance with known fields only\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: from_options with partial overrides\n113: - **GIVEN** a dict `{\"description\": \"My agent\"}`\n114: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options_dict)` is called\n115: - **THEN** only `description` SHALL be set; all other fields SHALL retain defaults\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: MetadataService.load_metadata\n120: \n121: The system SHALL load agent metadata from a workspace directory, trying `agent_metadata.yaml` first, then falling back to `agent.yaml` and `metadata.yaml`.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Load from primary file\n124: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` exists with valid YAML content\n125: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL parse the YAML, construct an `AgentMetadata` instance via Pydantic validation, and return it\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Fallback to agent.yaml\n129: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist but `{workspace}/agent.yaml` exists with valid content\n130: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n131: - **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `agent.yaml` and return the validated `AgentMetadata` instance\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Fallback to metadata.yaml\n134: - **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists but `{workspace}/metadata.yaml` exists\n135: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n136: - **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `metadata.yaml` and return the validated `AgentMetadata` instance\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: No metadata file found returns defaults\n139: - **GIVEN** none of `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` exist in the workspace\n140: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n141: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a new `AgentMetadata` instance with all default values (required fields unset, so Pydantic defaults apply for fields with defaults)\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Invalid YAML raises parse error\n144: - **GIVEN** a metadata file exists but contains malformed YAML (e.g., unbalanced brackets)\n145: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n146: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `yaml.YAMLError` or equivalent parsing exception\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Pydantic validation failure on load\n149: - **GIVEN** a metadata file contains `language: \"rust\"` (unsupported)\n150: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n151: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise a `ValidationError` from the `validate_language` validator\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Verbose logging on load\n154: - **GIVEN** `MetadataService(verbose=True)`\n155: - **WHEN** `load_metadata` is called\n156: - **THEN** it SHALL log which metadata file was loaded (or that defaults were used)\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: MetadataService.save_metadata\n161: \n162: The system SHALL persist `AgentMetadata` to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using specific YAML serialization settings.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Save with YAML formatting\n165: - **GIVEN** a valid `AgentMetadata` instance and an existing workspace directory\n166: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n167: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Exclude None fields on save\n170: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` instance with optional fields set to `None` (e.g., `description=None`, `region=None`)\n171: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n172: - **THEN** the YAML output SHALL exclude all `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Overwrite existing file\n175: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` already exists\n176: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n177: - **THEN** the file SHALL be overwritten with the new content\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Verbose logging on save\n180: - **GIVEN** `MetadataService(verbose=True)`\n181: - **WHEN** `save_metadata` is called\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL log the path where metadata was saved\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### Requirement: MetadataService.update_metadata\n187: \n188: The system SHALL load existing metadata, apply field updates from a dict, save the result, and return the updated instance.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Update existing fields\n191: - **GIVEN** valid metadata exists in the workspace with `language: \"python\"` and `port: 8080`\n192: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, {\"language\": \"java\", \"port\": 9090})` is called\n193: - **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata, apply the updates, save the result, and return an `AgentMetadata` with `language=\"java\"` and `port=9090`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Update with new optional fields\n196: - **GIVEN** valid metadata exists without `description` set\n197: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, {\"description\": \"My agent\"})` is called\n198: - **THEN** the returned `AgentMetadata` SHALL have `description=\"My agent\"` and the file SHALL be updated\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Update with invalid values rejects\n201: - **GIVEN** valid metadata exists\n202: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, {\"port\": 99999})` is called\n203: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise a `ValidationError` from the `validate_port` validator and the file SHALL NOT be modified\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Update with no existing metadata creates new\n206: - **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n207: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, {\"agent_name\": \"test\", \"entrypoint\": \"main.py\"})` is called\n208: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with defaults, apply the updates, save it, and return the instance\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Verbose logging on update\n211: - **GIVEN** `MetadataService(verbose=True)`\n212: - **WHEN** `update_metadata` is called\n213: - **THEN** it SHALL log which fields were updated\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ### Requirement: MetadataService.validate_workspace\n218: \n219: The system SHALL validate that a workspace path exists and is a directory, returning a boolean result.\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Valid workspace directory\n222: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}` exists as a directory\n223: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n224: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `True`\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n227: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist on the filesystem\n228: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n229: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `False`\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: Workspace is a file, not a directory\n232: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` points to a regular file\n233: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n234: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `False`\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ### Requirement: MetadataService._validate_python_workspace\n239: \n240: The system SHALL validate that a Python workspace contains at least one `.py` file in the root directory.\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Python files present\n243: - **GIVEN** the workspace root contains `main.py`\n244: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n245: - **THEN** the method SHALL complete without raising\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Multiple Python files present\n248: - **GIVEN** the workspace root contains `main.py` and `utils.py`\n249: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n250: - **THEN** the method SHALL complete without raising\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: No Python files raises error\n253: - **GIVEN** the workspace root contains no `*.py` files\n254: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n255: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ### Requirement: MetadataService._validate_java_workspace\n260: \n261: The system SHALL validate that a Java workspace contains a `pom.xml` file.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: pom.xml present\n264: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/pom.xml` exists\n265: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n266: - **THEN** the method SHALL complete without raising\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: pom.xml missing raises error\n269: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/pom.xml` does not exist\n270: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n271: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating `pom.xml` is required\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ### Requirement: Metadata file format\n276: \n277: The system SHALL use YAML as the serialization format for agent metadata with specific structural conventions.\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: YAML structure matches model fields\n280: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` with `agent_name=\"hello-agent\"`, `language=\"python\"`, `entrypoint=\"main.py\"`, `port=8080`\n281: - **WHEN** the metadata is saved to YAML\n282: - **THEN** the file SHALL contain keys `agent_name`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port` with corresponding values and no `None` fields\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: Complex nested fields serialized\n285: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` with `image={\"url\": \"my.registry/agent:v1\"}` and `k8s_deployment={\"name\": \"hello-agent\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n286: - **WHEN** the metadata is saved to YAML\n287: - **THEN** the YAML SHALL contain nested mappings for `image` and `k8s_deployment` with `indent=2`\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Field order preserved\n290: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` instance\n291: - **WHEN** the metadata is saved to YAML\n292: - **THEN** the key order in the YAML SHALL match the model field definition order (due to `sort_keys=False`)\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Round-trip load/save consistency\n295: - **GIVEN** a valid `AgentMetadata` instance saved to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n296: - **WHEN** the file is loaded back via `load_metadata`\n297: - **THEN** the reloaded instance SHALL have the same field values as the original (excluding `None` fields that were excluded on save)\n298: \n299: ## File changes\n300: \n301: | Action | File | Description |\n302: |--------|------|-------------|\n303: | Add/Modify | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | MetadataService class with load, save, update, validate operations |\n304: | Add/Modify | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | MetadataOptions dataclass with from_options classmethod |\n305: | Add/Modify | `agentcube/services/metadata_models.py` or inline | AgentMetadata Pydantic BaseModel with validators |\n306: | Add | `tests/services/test_metadata_service.py` | MetadataService unit tests |\n307: | Add | `tests/models/test_pack_models.py` | MetadataOptions and AgentMetadata unit tests |\n\n(End of file - total 307 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025: MetadataService дЄОжХ∞жНЃж®°еЮЛ вАФ Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentMetadata Pydantic model\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` with typed fields, defaults, descriptions, and validators for language, build_mode, and port.\n\n#### Scenario: Construct with required fields only\n- **GIVEN** input `agent_name=\"test-agent\"` and `entrypoint=\"main.py\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(agent_name=\"test-agent\", entrypoint=\"main.py\")` is constructed\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL have defaults `language=\"python\"`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=\"local\"`, `requirements_file=\"requirements.txt\"`, `registry_url=\"\"`, `registry_username=\"\"`, `registry_password=\"\"`, and all `Optional` fields as `None`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775861192895,"end":1775861192912}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861194201,"sessionID":"ses_2866cdffeffebbLEVIAe132gIZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79935950001dtG11IQ2QlHMqo","messageID":"msg_d79933edf001RiI5w9NR1fY3Jv","sessionID":"ses_2866cdffeffebbLEVIAe132gIZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8721fca023e74ee588347722","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 вАФ MetadataService дЄОжХ∞жНЃж®°еЮЛ вАФ Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-025/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-025/design.md`, `changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** None\n9: \n10: ## T1. AgentMetadata Pydantic Model вАФ Field Definitions\n11: \n12: - [ ] 1.1 Define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n13: - [ ] 1.2 Add 2 required fields: `agent_name: str` (no default), `entrypoint: str` (no default)\n14: - [ ] 1.3 Add 3 validated fields with defaults: `language: str = \"python\"`, `port: int = 8080`, `build_mode: str = \"local\"`\n15: - [ ] 1.4 Add 4 string-default optional fields: `requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"`, `registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n16: - [ ] 1.5 Add 13 `None`-default optional fields: `description`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n17: - [ ] 1.6 Add `Field(...)` descriptions for all 22 fields\n18: \n19: **Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata; m = AgentMetadata(agent_name='test', entrypoint='main.py'); print(len(m.model_fields))\"` outputs 22\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## T2. AgentMetadata вАФ Language Validator\n24: \n25: - [ ] 2.1 Implement `@field_validator(\"language\", mode=\"before\")` that normalizes input to lowercase\n26: - [ ] 2.2 Accept `\"python\"` and `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n27: - [ ] 2.3 Return `\"python\"` as default when input is `None`\n28: - [ ] 2.4 Raise `ValueError` with message `\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'.\"` for unsupported values\n29: \n30: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage -v` all pass\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## T3. AgentMetadata вАФ Build Mode Validator\n35: \n36: - [ ] 3.1 Implement `@field_validator(\"build_mode\", mode=\"before\")` that normalizes input to lowercase\n37: - [ ] 3.2 Accept `\"local\"` and `\"cloud\"` (case-insensitive)\n38: - [ ] 3.3 Return `\"local\"` as default when input is `None`\n39: - [ ] 3.4 Raise `ValueError` with message `\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'.\"` for unsupported values\n40: \n41: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode -v` all pass\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## T4. AgentMetadata вАФ Port Validator\n46: \n47: - [ ] 4.1 Implement `@field_validator(\"port\")` (default mode, after type coercion)\n48: - [ ] 4.2 Accept ports in range `1..65535`\n49: - [ ] 4.3 Raise `ValueError` with message `\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\"` for out-of-range values\n50: \n51: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidatePort -v` all pass\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## T5. AgentMetadata вАФ Serialization Tests\n56: \n57: - [ ] 5.1 Test `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` excludes all `None` fields\n58: - [ ] 5.2 Test required fields and defaults are present in dumped output\n59: - [ ] 5.3 Test minimal construction (required fields only) produces correct defaults\n60: - [ ] 5.4 Test full construction (all fields) preserves all values\n61: \n62: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidCreation -v` and `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataModelDump -v` all pass\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## T6. MetadataOptions Dataclass вАФ Field Definitions\n67: \n68: - [ ] 6.1 Define `MetadataOptions` as a `@dataclass` in `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n69: - [ ] 6.2 Add 14 optional fields with correct defaults:\n70:   - `agent_name: Optional[str] = None`\n71:   - `language: Optional[str] = \"python\"`\n72:   - `entrypoint: Optional[str] = None`\n73:   - `port: Optional[int] = 8080`\n74:   - `build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"`\n75:   - `requirements_file: Optional[str] = None`\n76:   - `description: Optional[str] = None`\n77:   - `workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n78:   - `router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n79:   - `readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n80:   - `readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080`\n81:   - `registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n82:   - `registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n83:   - `registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n84:   - `agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n85: \n86: **Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; o = MetadataOptions(); print(len(o.__dataclass_fields__))\"` outputs 15\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## T7. MetadataOptions вАФ from_options Classmethod\n91: \n92: - [ ] 7.1 Implement `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any])` classmethod\n93: - [ ] 7.2 Define `known_fields` set with all 15 field names\n94: - [ ] 7.3 Filter input dict to only known fields (silently ignore unknown keys)\n95: - [ ] 7.4 Return `cls(**filtered)` instance\n96: \n97: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptionsFromOptions -v` all pass\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## T8. MetadataOptions вАФ Default Values Tests\n102: \n103: - [ ] 8.1 Test all 15 fields have expected default values when constructed with no arguments\n104: - [ ] 8.2 Test `from_options({})` returns instance with all defaults\n105: - [ ] 8.3 Test `from_options` with partial dict sets only specified fields\n106: - [ ] 8.4 Test `from_options` with unknown keys ignores them\n107: \n108: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py -v` all pass\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## T9. MetadataService вАФ Class Skeleton and Constants\n113: \n114: - [ ] 9.1 Define `MetadataService` class in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n115: - [ ] 9.2 Add class constant `METADATA_FILES: List[str] = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]`\n116: - [ ] 9.3 Add `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)` storing `self.verbose`\n117: \n118: **Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService; s = MetadataService(verbose=True); print(s.METADATA_FILES, s.verbose)\"` outputs correct values\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## T10. MetadataService вАФ load_metadata\n123: \n124: - [ ] 10.1 Implement `load_metadata(workspace_path: Path) -> Optional[AgentMetadata]`\n125: - [ ] 10.2 Iterate through `METADATA_FILES` in priority order\n126: - [ ] 10.3 For first existing file: open, `yaml.safe_load()`, handle `None` result as `{}`, return `AgentMetadata(**data)`\n127: - [ ] 10.4 Return `None` if no metadata file exists\n128: - [ ] 10.5 Do not catch `yaml.YAMLError` or `ValidationError` вАФ let them propagate\n129: \n130: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestLoadMetadataPrimaryExists -v`, `::TestLoadMetadataFirstFallback -v`, `::TestLoadMetadataSecondFallback -v`, `::TestLoadMetadataNoneExist -v` all pass\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## T11. MetadataService вАФ save_metadata\n135: \n136: - [ ] 11.1 Implement `save_metadata(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n137: - [ ] 11.2 Always write to `agent_metadata.yaml` (canonical filename)\n138: - [ ] 11.3 Use `metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)` for data\n139: - [ ] 11.4 Call `yaml.dump(data, f, default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)`\n140: \n141: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip -v`, `::TestSaveMetadataExcludeNone -v`, `::TestSaveMetadataFormat -v` all pass\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ## T12. MetadataService вАФ update_metadata\n146: \n147: - [ ] 12.1 Implement `update_metadata(workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata`\n148: - [ ] 12.2 Call `load_metadata()` вАФ if `None`, create default `AgentMetadata` using `updates` for required fields and `workspace_path.name` fallback for `agent_name`\n149: - [ ] 12.3 Call `existing.model_copy(update=updates)` for immutable merge with re-validation\n150: - [ ] 12.4 Call `save_metadata()` with merged result\n151: - [ ] 12.5 Return merged `AgentMetadata` instance\n152: \n153: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestUpdateMetadataMerge -v`, `::TestUpdateMetadataCreateNew -v` all pass\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## T13. MetadataService вАФ validate_workspace\n158: \n159: - [ ] 13.1 Implement `validate_workspace(workspace_path: Path) -> bool`\n160: - [ ] 13.2 Return `self.load_metadata(workspace_path) is not None`\n161: - [ ] 13.3 Note: This checks metadata file presence only, not filesystem structure\n162: \n163: **Verification:** `python -c \"\n164: from pathlib import Path; from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n165: s = MetadataService()\n166: import tempfile; ws = Path(tempfile.mkdtemp())\n167: (ws / 'agent_metadata.yaml').write_text('agent_name: t\\nentrypoint: m\\n')\n168: print(s.validate_workspace(ws))  # True\n169: (ws / 'agent_metadata.yaml').unlink()\n170: print(s.validate_workspace(ws))  # False\n171: \"`\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ## T14. MetadataService вАФ _validate_python_workspace\n176: \n177: - [ ] 14.1 Implement `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n178: - [ ] 14.2 Check at least one `*.py` file exists in workspace root via `workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\")`\n179: - [ ] 14.3 Raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` if no `.py` files\n180: - [ ] 14.4 Check requirements file exists (use `metadata.requirements_file` or default `\"requirements.txt\"`)\n181: - [ ] 14.5 Raise `ValueError(f\"Dependency file not found: {req_file}\")` if missing\n182: \n183: **Verification:** Manual test with workspace containing/missing `.py` and `requirements.txt` files\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## T15. MetadataService вАФ _validate_java_workspace\n188: \n189: - [ ] 15.1 Implement `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n190: - [ ] 15.2 Check `pom.xml` exists in workspace root\n191: - [ ] 15.3 Raise `ValueError(\"pom.xml is required for Java projects\")` if missing\n192: \n193: **Verification:** Manual test with workspace containing/missing `pom.xml`\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ## T16. Round-trip Consistency Test\n198: \n199: - [ ] 16.1 Create `AgentMetadata` with mix of required, default, and optional fields\n200: - [ ] 16.2 Save to YAML via `MetadataService.save_metadata()`\n201: - [ ] 16.3 Load back via `MetadataService.load_metadata()`\n202: - [ ] 16.4 Verify all non-None field values match original\n203: \n204: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip -v` passes\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ## T17. Error Handling Verification\n209: \n210: - [ ] 17.1 Verify malformed YAML raises `yaml.YAMLError`\n211: - [ ] 17.2 Verify unsupported language in YAML raises `ValidationError`\n212: - [ ] 17.3 Verify missing required field raises `ValidationError`\n213: - [ ] 17.4 Verify port out of range in update raises `ValidationError` and does not modify file\n214: \n215: **Verification:** All covered by existing test classes `TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage`, `TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode`, `TestAgentMetadataValidatePort`\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## T18. Linting and Type Checking\n220: \n221: - [ ] 18.1 Run `ruff check` on `metadata_service.py` and `pack_models.py` вАФ no violations\n222: - [ ] 18.2 Run `mypy` on `metadata_service.py` and `pack_models.py` вАФ no type errors\n223: \n224: **Verification:** `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` and `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` both pass\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Task Dependencies\n229: \n230: ```\n231: T1 (AgentMetadata fields)\n232: вФЬвФАвФА T2 (language validator)\n233: вФЬвФАвФА T3 (build_mode validator)\n234: вФЬвФАвФА T4 (port validator)\n235: вФФвФАвФА T5 (serialization tests)\n236: \n237: T6 (MetadataOptions fields)\n238: вФФвФАвФА T7 (from_options)\n239:     вФФвФАвФА T8 (defaults tests)\n240: \n241: T9 (MetadataService skeleton)\n242: вФЬвФАвФА T10 (load_metadata)\n243: вФЬвФАвФА T11 (save_metadata)\n244: вФЬвФАвФА T12 (update_metadata)\n245: вФЬвФАвФА T13 (validate_workspace)\n246: вФЬвФАвФА T14 (_validate_python_workspace)\n247: вФФвФАвФА T15 (_validate_java_workspace)\n248: \n249: T10, T11, T12\n250: вФФвФАвФА T16 (round-trip test)\n251: \n252: T2, T3, T4, T10, T12\n253: вФФвФАвФА T17 (error handling)\n254: \n255: T1-T17\n256: вФФвФАвФА T18 (linting + type check)\n257: ```\n258: \n259: ## Parallelizable Groups\n260: \n261: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n262: |-------|-------|---------------|\n263: | G1 | T1, T6, T9 | None |\n264: | G2 | T2, T3, T4 | T1 |\n265: | G3 | T7 | T6 |\n266: | G4 | T10, T11, T13, T14, T15 | T9 |\n267: | G5 | T5, T8 | T2, T3, T4, T7 |\n268: | G6 | T12 | T10, T11 |\n269: | G7 | T16, T17 | T10, T11, T12, T2, T3, T4 |\n270: | G8 | T18 | T1-T17 |\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: ## Acceptance Criteria\n275: \n276: | # | Criterion | Command |\n277: |---|-----------|---------|\n278: | AC1 | AgentMetadata has 22 fields with correct types and defaults | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidCreation -v` |\n279: | AC2 | Language validator accepts python/java, rejects others | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage -v` |\n280: | AC3 | Build mode validator accepts local/cloud, rejects others | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode -v` |\n281: | AC4 | Port validator accepts 1-65535, rejects out of range | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidatePort -v` |\n282: | AC5 | model_dump(exclude_none=True) works correctly | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataModelDump -v` |\n283: | AC6 | MetadataOptions has 15 fields with correct defaults | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptionsDefaults -v` |\n284: | AC7 | from_options filters known fields, ignores unknown | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptionsFromOptions -v` |\n285: | AC8 | load_metadata tries primary вЖТ fallback1 вЖТ fallback2 вЖТ None | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -k LoadMetadata -v` |\n286: | AC9 | save_metadata writes clean YAML with correct formatting | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -k SaveMetadata -v` |\n287: | AC10 | update_metadata merges and validates correctly | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -k UpdateMetadata -v` |\n288: | AC11 | validate_workspace returns boolean based on metadata presence | Manual verification |\n289: | AC12 | _validate_python_workspace checks .py and requirements file | Manual verification |\n290: | AC13 | _validate_java_workspace checks pom.xml | Manual verification |\n291: | AC14 | Round-trip save вЖТ load produces equivalent values | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip -v` |\n292: | AC15 | All tests pass | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py -v` |\n293: | AC16 | No linting violations | `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` |\n294: | AC17 | No type errors | `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` |\n\n(End of file - total 294 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 вАФ MetadataService дЄОжХ∞жНЃж®°еЮЛ вАФ Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-025/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-025/design.md`, `changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n## T1. AgentMetadata Pydantic Model вАФ Field Definitions\n\n- [ ] 1.1 Define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- [ ] 1.2 Add 2 required fields: `agent_name: str` (no default), `entrypoint: str` (no default)\n- [ ] 1.3 Add 3 validated fields with defaults: `language: str = \"python\"`, `port: int = 8080`, `build_mode: str = \"local\"`\n- [ ] 1.4 Add 4 string-default optional fields: `requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"`, `registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n- [ ] 1.5 Add 13 `None`-default optional fields: `description`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n- [ ] 1.6 Add `Field(...)` descriptions for all 22 fields\n\n**Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata; m = AgentMetadata(agent_name='test', entrypoint='main.py'); print(len(m.model_fields))\"` outputs 22\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775861194189,"end":1775861194199}}}}
